    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_12_listing_6",
      "firm_id": "sybil_12",
      "description": "Hey there! I'm parting ways with my trusty ride, and honestly, it\u2019s been such a joy to drive. It\u2019s in really nice shape, runs super smoothly, and has been well-loved over the years. If you\u2019re looking for a dependable car that still looks great and feels solid on the road, this is the one for you! I've taken great care of it, and it's totally ready for its next adventure. Come take it for a spin and see for yourself!",
      "price": 32500.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 45
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_13_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_13",
      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) features the refined 3.6L M96 flat-six with VarioCam Plus, delivering a linear power band and distinct mechanical howl. The G96 6-speed manual transaxle offers precise shift throws and crisp engagement. Critically, the IMS bearing has been addressed with a dual-row ceramic upgrade, and the rear main seal (RMS) remains bone dry. The suspension maintains its factory composure with refreshed control arms and dampers, ensuring the legendary rear-engine weight bias provides maximum tactile feedback through the hydraulic steering rack. While showing minor cosmetic patina consistent with spirited use, the drivetrain and chassis are dialed for the enthusiast who values technical integrity and performance over trailer-queen status.",
